speaking,
which
nothing
else
had
so
effectually
done
before;
and
she
asked
Bingley
whether
he
meant
to
make
any
stay
in
the
country
at
present.
A
few
weeks,
he
believed.
"When
you
have
killed
all
your
own
birds,
Mr.
Bingley,"
said
her
mother,
"I
beg
you
will
come
here,
and
shoot
as
many
as
you
please
on
Mr.
Bennet's
manor.
I
am
sure
he
will
be
vastly
happy
to
