Elizabeth's
misery
increased,
at
such
unnecessary,
such
officious
attention!
Were
the
same
fair
prospect
to
arise
at
present
as
had
flattered
them
a
year
ago,
every
thing,
she
was
persuaded,
would
be
hastening
to
the
same
vexatious
conclusion.
At
that
instant,
she
felt
that
years
of
happiness
could
not
make
Jane
or
herself
amends
for
moments
of
such
painful
